.TH SYSWATCH 1 "2026-05-01" "0.1.0" "SysWatch Manual"
.SH NAME
syswatch \- a high-performance Linux system monitor TUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B syswatch
.SH DESCRIPTION
SysWatch is a terminal UI (TUI) system monitor for Linux. It provides
real-time, colour-coded views of CPU per-core utilization, memory usage,
disk I/O, network bandwidth, and a searchable, sortable process list.
.PP
Data is sampled every 500 ms. The UI renders at up to 30 fps with
near-zero CPU overhead. Braille-character sparkline graphs (Unicode
U+2800 block) provide high-resolution trend history.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.TP
.B F1 / F2 / F3 / F4
Switch to Overview / Processes / Network / Disk tab.
.TP
.B Tab
Cycle through tabs.
.TP
.B Up / Down  (or k / j)
Scroll the process list.
.TP
.B /
Enter filter mode. Type to search by process name.
.TP
.B Esc / Enter
Exit filter mode.
.TP
.B f
Cycle sort column: CPU% → MEM% → PID → Name.
.TP
.B k
Send SIGTERM to the selected process.
.TP
.B q / Ctrl-C
Quit.
